# Unprotected Admin Functionality with Unpredictable URL

## Vulnerability Type
Broken Access Control

## Difficulty
Apprentice

## Platform
PortSwigger Web Security Academy

## Goal
Solve the lab by accessing the admin panel and deleting the user "carlos".

## Root Cause
The application exposed an administrative panel without proper authorization checks. Although the admin URL was unpredictable, its location was disclosed within the application's source code.

## Exploitation Steps
1. Browse the application
2. View the page source code
3. Identify the exposed admin URL inside JavaScript
4. Access the admin panel directly
5. Delete the user "carlos"

## Impact
An attacker can gain unauthorized access to administrative functionality and perform privileged actions.

## Prevention
- Enforce server-side authorization checks
- Restrict access to admin endpoints
- Implement role-based access control
- Avoid exposing sensitive endpoints in client-side code

## What I Learned
This lab helped me understand how hidden administrative functionality can still become accessible if sensitive endpoints are exposed in client-side source code.
